4 Sec. 3. FIRST ANNUAL REPORT OF THE JOINT GOVERNMENT
5 OVERSIGHT AND ACCOUNTABILITY COMMITTEE
6 The Joint Government Oversight and Accountability Committee shall
7 include in its first annual report required by 2 V.S.A. § 972(a)(3) an analysis of
8 whether the General Assembly should empower the Committee to issue
9 subpoenas and administer oaths in connection with its examination and
10 investigation of matters of government oversight and accountability related to
11 issues of significant public concern. The Committee shall also include in its
12 report a recommendation for whether the General Assembly should add a staff
13 member dedicated to supporting the Committee in its work.
